race.comment: ROSES IMMINENTE (18) talented on her day and a win looks imminent third-up. Warmed up late when a respectable fourth over 1600m at Randwick in this class. Since fitted with a 900m trial and the blinkers come off. Gets the right setup again and doesn't have to improve much to win this. SHE WITHIN (10) lightly raced mare proven at this level. Returned from a let up with a narrow win over 1200m at Moruya. Has further improvement to come with the key jockey change. Top-three player. FINGERS HUNTER (1) strong mare who raced in better company last prep. Solid through the line on resumption when a slashing fifth over 1200m at Randwick. Looking for the trip and is a second-up winner. SPEEDY HENRY (11) handy gelding set to deliver third-up. Shouldered the 60kg when a respectable sixth over 1300m at Taree. Looking for the trip and worth more than a passing glance. WARRIOR FOR PEACE (12) back without a trial and has a decent first-up record. Adept in all conditions.
